# Step 5: Create Dockerfile

```bash
nano Dockerfile
```

Paste:

```dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17
COPY target/java-cicd-app-1.0.jar app.jar
CMD ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```

---

# Step 6: Test Docker Locally

```bash
docker build -t java-cicd-app:latest .
```

Run:

```bash
docker run --rm java-cicd-app:latest
```

Expected:

```text
Java CI/CD Pipeline Running Successfully
```

Stop:

```text
control + C
```

---

# Step 7: Initialize Docker Swarm

```bash
docker swarm init
```

If already initialized, ignore the error.

---

# Step 8: Deploy on Docker Swarm

```bash
docker service create --name java-service --replicas 1 java-cicd-app:latest
```

Check:

```bash
docker service ls
```

Expected:

```text
java-service   replicated   1/1   java-cicd-app:latest
```

Remove service before Jenkins testing:

```bash
docker service rm java-service
```

---

# Step 9: Create Jenkinsfile

```bash
nano Jenkinsfile
```

Paste:

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    triggers {
        cron('H/5 * * * *')
    }

    stages {
        stage('Build Maven') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t java-cicd-app:latest .'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy Docker Swarm') {
            steps {
                sh '''
                docker swarm init || true
                docker service rm java-service || true
                docker service create --name java-service --replicas 1 java-cicd-app:latest
                '''
            }
        }

        stage('Check Service') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker service ls'
            }
        }
    }
}
```

