# Step 10: Push Project to GitHub

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Java Maven CI CD Docker Swarm project"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/vardhanacharya/program2.git
git push -u origin main
```

If remote already exists:

```bash
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/vardhanacharya/program2.git
git push
```

---

# Step 11: Open Jenkins

Start Jenkins:

```bash
brew services start jenkins-lts
```

Open browser:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

---

# Step 12: Create Jenkins Pipeline Job

1. Click **New Item**
2. Enter name:

```text
program2
```

3. Select **Pipeline**
4. Click **OK**
5. Go to **Pipeline** section
6. Select:

```text
Pipeline script from SCM
```

7. SCM:

```text
Git
```

8. Repository URL:

```text
https://github.com/vardhanacharya/program2.git
```

9. Branch:

```text
*/main
```

10. Script Path:

```text
Jenkinsfile
```

11. Click **Save**

---

